[normal]There are a few improvements in the science in AR5 – the IPCC has dumped the hockey stick, and has dropped claims that hurricanes will increase in intensity and that flooding and drought will become more serious.  The main shortcoming is that the report is
[normal] unable to explain the 16 
[normal]or 17 year pause in global warming.   Next, despite the expenditure of hundreds of £M on climate models they do not track global temperature accurately. The (leaked) final draft Summary for Policy Makers identified that 
[normal]“Models do
[normal] not generally reproduce the observed reduction in surface warming trend over the last 10
[normal]–15 years”
